article.description: — Bryce Hopkins' 24 points helped Providence defeat Rhode Island 84-69 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Hopkins scores 24, Providence beats Rhode Island 84-69
article.linkText: Hopkins scores 24, Providence beats Rhode Island 84-69
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- — Bryce Hopkins' 24 points helped Providence defeat Rhode Island 84-69 on Saturday night. Hopkins also had seven rebounds for the Friars (7-1). Devin Carter scored 17 points and added 11 rebounds. Jayden Pierre shot 3 for 7 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 5 of 5 from the free throw line to finish with 12 points. Jaden House finished with 18 points for the Rams (5-3). David Fuchs added 11 points and six rebounds for Rhode Island. Luis Kortright also put up 11 points and four assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
